<li>Mutations that inactivate the repressor function of GcvA allow growth on the LM plate because the lgcvT-lacZ gene fusion is no longer repressed and therefore there is sufﬁcient b-galac-tosidase activity for growth on this medium .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9733689" target="_blank">9733689</a>]<br></li>
<li>However , the double mutant does not grow on an LM plate supplemented with serine , inosine , and TPEG ( an inhibitor of b-galactosidase ) when wt gcvA is supplied in trans because GcvA , in the presence of inosine , represses the lgcvT-lacZ gene fusion , resulting in insufﬁcient b-galactosidase activity for growth on lactose .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9733689" target="_blank">9733689</a>]<br></li>
<li>Although strain GS 1039 carries n SczJT : :1 acZ translational gene fusion on an integrated i.phage , when wt gcriA is supplied iiz trans this lysogen can not grow o n a LM plate supplemented with serine , inosinc and T P E G ( a competitive inhibitor of [ jgalactosidase ; Miller , 1992 ) because GcvA , in the presence of inosine , represses the fusion resulting in insufficient [ j-galactosidase expression to support growth on lactose .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10463182" target="_blank">10463182</a>]<br></li>
<li>A wide range of environmental stimuli affect the expression of the sRNAs including oxidative-stress ( OxyR activates OxyS ) ; cell surface stress ( RcsB activates RprA ) ; glycine status of the cell ( GcvA activates GcvB ) ; osmotic imbalance ( OmpR activates OmrA/B ) ; quality of carbon source/growth rate [ McaS ; transcription factor ( s ) unknown ] ; low temperature [ DsrA ; transcription factor ( s ) unknown ] and O tension ( ArcA-ArcB 2 represses ArzA under anaerobic conditions ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=22250746" target="_blank">22250746</a>]<br></li>
<li>If wt gcvA is supplied in trans , growth of the double mutant on a GM plate supplemented with glycine resumes because GcvA , in the presence of glycine , activates expression of the genes encoding the GCV enzyme system , resulting in cleavage of glycine and the production of C-1 units needed for serine production .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9733689" target="_blank">9733689</a>]<br></li>
<li>If wt gc-z ~ Ais supplied in t r a m , growth on a G M plate supplcniented with glycine occurs because GcvA , in the presencc o f glycine , activates expression of the GCV enzyme systcni resulting in cleavage of glycine and the production o f C - 1 units .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10463182" target="_blank">10463182</a>]<br></li>
<li>In the presence of both glycine and purines , the activator function of GcvA is dominant ( Stauffer & Stauffer , 1994 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11065369" target="_blank">11065369</a>]<br></li>
<li>To define amino acids i n GcvA important for irs repressor function , we attempted to isolate gczjA mutnnts th : it encoded proteins that could no longer repress g c i ~ T : : lacZ expression in the presence of purines but could activate expression in the presence of glycine .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10463182" target="_blank">10463182</a>]<br></li>
<li>Although the a-galactosidase levels were induced about % fold in the presence of glycine in the GS852 + 11-213 lysogen , the induced levels RESULTS AND DISCUSSION were still about 2-5-fold lower than in the control Effects on gcvT : : / at2 expression of separating GcvA - lysogen .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9802028" target="_blank">9802028</a>]<br></li>
<li>Overexpression o f gcrlA results in constitutive expression o f 11 gcr ~ T : : lacZ fusion in the absence of exogenous glycine and in the presence of exogenous purines ( Christ & Stauffer , 199.5 ) , and thus it appears critical that GcvA levels Lire maintained within a narrow range for the cell ~ ~ ~ ~ to respond appropriately t o a glycine-inducing o r purine-repressing signal .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10463182" target="_blank">10463182</a>]<br></li>
<li>Therefore , the activation of the omr-lacZ fusions by pYqjA-YqjB , pYgdD-GcvA or pFadR requires EnvZ-OmpR .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=16359331" target="_blank">16359331</a>]<br></li>
<li>In the wild-type strain , pYqjA-YqjB , pYgdD-GcvA and pOmpR activate both fusions and pFadR activates omrB-lacZ ( Fig. 3 ) , with the strongest signal from pYgdD-GcvA .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=16359331" target="_blank">16359331</a>]<br></li>
<li>Surprisingly , even though plasmids pYqjA-YqjB and pYgdD-GcvA act upstream of OmpR to activate omrA-lacZ and omrB-lacZ fusions , they had a stronger effect on these fusions than pOmpR itself ( Fig. 3 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=16359331" target="_blank">16359331</a>]<br></li>
<li>Regulation of the gcv operon by GcvA and GcvR is part of a growing number of prokaryotic regulatory systems involving an activator -RCB- antiactivator complex , including TraR -RCB- TraM regulation of conjugal transfer of the Ti plasmid in Agrobacterium tumefaciens ( Hwang et al. , 1999 ) , NifA -RCB- NifL regulation of nitrogen ﬁxation in Klebsiella pneumoniae ( Narberhaus et al. , 1995 ) , ComK -RCB- MecA -RCB- ClpC regulation of competence in Ba-cillus subtilis ( Turgay et al. , 1998 ) and CRP -RCB- CytR regulation of operons encoding the nucleoside transport and biosynthesis enzymes ( Valentin-Hansen et al. , 1996 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11495998" target="_blank">11495998</a>]<br></li>
