<li>Bending of the DNA by Lrp and GcvA allows GcvA bound to sites 32 to interact with the α-carboxy-terminal domain of RNA polymerase , permitting stimulation of RNAP , and activation of transcription .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12101307" target="_blank">12101307</a>]<br></li>
