<li>Since GcvA negatively autoregulates its own expression , a plasmid and a chromosomal copy of gcvA present in the same cell may allow more autoregulation and cause lower levels of gcvA than expected .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10074087" target="_blank">10074087</a>]<br></li>
<li>We report here that , in addition to its negative role at its own promoter , GcvA at the gcvA locus activates transcription of a divergent , overlapping promoter encoding a short RNA transcript that is not translated .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10972807" target="_blank">10972807</a>]<br></li>
