<li>The addition of glycine ( 3 mM ) to the GMS assays did not show any alteration in either GcvA 's binding afinity to the three sites in the control region , nor were there any changes in the calculated bend angles induced by GcvA binding to the DNA ( data not shown ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12101307" target="_blank">12101307</a>]<br></li>
