<li>RESULTS Effects of glycine on GcvA binding to the gcv control region and bending DNA Most LTTRs have been shown to-bind to their promoters in the absence of their respective co-inducers ( Schell , 1993 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12101307" target="_blank">12101307</a>]<br></li>
<li>GcvA bound to the gcv promoter region and induced a bend in the DNA in the absence of glycine ( Fig. 3 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12101307" target="_blank">12101307</a>]<br></li>
<li>To identify which sequences of DNA are necessary for binding of GcvA to the gcv and gcvA control regions , DNase I footprinting assays were performed .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=7665470" target="_blank">7665470</a>]<br></li>
<li>GcvA binding to the gcv control region induces DNA 32 bending .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12101307" target="_blank">12101307</a>, <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12101307" target="_blank">12101307</a>]<br></li>
<li>The question of whether binding of GcvA to its target sites in gcv results in looping of the intervening DNA will be pursued in future studies .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=7665470" target="_blank">7665470</a>]<br></li>
<li>121 The mutations in the conserved sequence of site 1 are involved in DNA conformation Recent experiments demonstrated that GcvA bends DNA when it binds to any of the three binding sites in the gcv control region ( G. Stauffer , unpublished results ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11065369" target="_blank">11065369</a>]<br></li>
<li>GcvA binds to three sites in the gcv control region ( Fig .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9611815" target="_blank">9611815</a>]<br></li>
<li>GcvA binds to three sites in the gcv control region , from bases -271 to -242 , -242 to -214 and -69 to -34 , relative to the transcription initiation site ( Fig .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9802028" target="_blank">9802028</a>]<br></li>
<li>Binding of GcvA to all three sites in the gcv control region is required for purinemediated repression of the gcv operon , whereas binding of GcvA to the two upstream sites is required for glycine-medi-ated induction .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9733689" target="_blank">9733689</a>]<br></li>
<li>Previous work showed that binding of GcvA to three sites in the gcv control region is required for repression of a gcvTlacZ fusion ( 32 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9733689" target="_blank">9733689</a>]<br></li>
<li>To test whether the altered binding afﬁnities demonstrated in the DNase I footprint analysis correlated with diminished GcvA regulation of gcv in vivo , translational fusions of the mutated gcv DNA fragments to the lacZ gene were made and cloned into lgt2 .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=7665470" target="_blank">7665470</a>]<br></li>
<li>It is not clear whether the bands with the slowest mobility are due to the binding of additional molecules of GcvA or whether they result from the binding of other factors present in the control extracts that are also able to-bind to gcvA DNA .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=7665470" target="_blank">7665470</a>]<br></li>
<li>Because the V32A GcvA protein displayed an altered GMS pattern compared to that of the wt GcvA protein , we wanted to determine if the mutant protein was binding to GcvA sites 1 , 2 , and 3 or if it was binding nonspeciﬁcally to the DNA .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9733689" target="_blank">9733689</a>]<br></li>
<li>Initially we tested whether GcvA binding alone induces a bend in DNA .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12101307" target="_blank">12101307</a>]<br></li>
<li>Binding of GcvA to sites 32 results in about a 100 ° bend in the DNA .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12101307" target="_blank">12101307</a>]<br></li>
<li>Mobility-shift assay for binding of GcvA to the 464 bp BamHI -- SspI WT , 1-A and 1-B fragments .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11065369" target="_blank">11065369</a>]<br></li>
<li>It should be noted , however , that the degree of protection of site 1 in the site 2 and 3 double mutant varied slightly between experiments ; sometimes a slight decrease in binding of GcvA to site 1 was noted .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=7665470" target="_blank">7665470</a>]<br></li>
<li>When site 1 was mutated , binding of GcvA to this site was prevented , although protection of sites 2 and 3 appeared to be unaffected ( lanes 19 to 22 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=7665470" target="_blank">7665470</a>]<br></li>
<li>Although the binding of GcvA to site 2 did not appear to be affected when site 3 was mutated , the binding of GcvA to site 3 was at least partially dependent upon binding of GcvA to site 2 ( Fig. 6 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=7665470" target="_blank">7665470</a>]<br></li>
<li>One possibility is the inability of single-base changes to eliminate binding of GcvA to site 1 .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11065369" target="_blank">11065369</a>]<br></li>
<li>Conversely , if CRP 's role is to interfere with repression by GcvA , then CRP would be expected to regulate normally when the repressor function is intact but would have no role when GcvAF31A can not repress ( in a gcvR strain ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10074087" target="_blank">10074087</a>]<br></li>
<li>However , evidence suggest that Lrp s role is structural , bending the PgcvT DNA to allow a GcvA Æ RNAP interaction [ 14 ] and CRP s role is to antagonize GcvA-mediated repression [ 15 ] .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15621456" target="_blank">15621456</a>]<br></li>
<li>However , the dependence of the CRP effect on the repressor function of GcvA suggests that its role is to antagonize GcvA-mediated repression .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12101307" target="_blank">12101307</a>]<br></li>
<li>One model proposed for gcv regulation is that Lrp plays a structural role , bending the DNA to allow GcvA to function as either an activator or a repressor in response to environmental signals .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10217490" target="_blank">10217490</a>]<br></li>
<li>Although the results of this study show that GcvA also induces a bend in the DNA , it is not known whether the GcvA-induced DNA bending plays a direct role in GcvA-mediated regulation of the gcv operon .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12101307" target="_blank">12101307</a>]<br></li>
<li>Although our results indicate that CRP 's role is to inhibit repression by GcvA at the gcv promoter , it is still possible that direct contact occurs between CRP and RNAP via DNA bending at gcv .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10074087" target="_blank">10074087</a>]<br></li>
<li>The results from this study are consistent with a model where CRP 's role in the regulation of gcv is to interfere with repression by GcvA , rather than to activate transcription via interactions with RNAP .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10074087" target="_blank">10074087</a>]<br></li>
<li>GS986 served as the control strain to demonstrate that multi-copy gcvR can not cause repression in the absence of GcvA .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11065369" target="_blank">11065369</a>]<br></li>
<li>Such mutations would be useful in understanding the mechanism of the GcvA -RCB- GcvRmediated repression system .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11065369" target="_blank">11065369</a>]<br></li>
<li>To distinguish between these two possible roles for CRP , the positive-control ( PC ) gcvA mutant gcvAF31A ( 16 ) was used to separate the activation and repression functions of GcvA .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10074087" target="_blank">10074087</a>]<br></li>
<li>Due to the dual action of GcvA , it is possible that CRP interferes with repression by GcvA or facilitates activation by GcvA , since both scenarios can explain the phenotypes of the Dcrp and the Dcrp DgcvA strains .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10074087" target="_blank">10074087</a>]<br></li>
<li>It is possible that the difference is related to the mechanism GcvA employs to switch between activation and repression .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11065369" target="_blank">11065369</a>]<br></li>
<li>Since the GS1053 +2 l - , , , lysogen showed a significant decrease in activity compared to the + 11-213 lysogen , it is likely that although the absolute distance of GcvA sites 3 and 2 relative to the gcv promoter can be lengthened , the increase is limited to a few helical turns without loss of activation and repression .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9802028" target="_blank">9802028</a>]<br></li>
<li>There is evidence that GcvA must bind to its three target sites for repression ( 47 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10074087" target="_blank">10074087</a>]<br></li>
<li>Previous studies suggested that all three GcvA binding sites are required for repression by GcvA , but only sites 2 and 3 are necessary for activation ( Wilson et al. , 1995 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11065369" target="_blank">11065369</a>]<br></li>
<li>Furthermore , since mutations in any of the three GcvA binding sites result in reduced repression ( Wilson et al. , 1995 ; Wonderling et al. , 2000 ) , at least part of the repression response of the gcv operon likely requires that a GcvR -RCB- GcvA repressor complex be bound to gcv DNA .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12101307" target="_blank">12101307</a>]<br></li>
<li>Since all three GcvA binding sites are required for normal repression of the gcv operon ( Wilson et al. , 1995 ; Wonderling et al. , 2000 ) , it is likely that GcvA and GcvR form a repression loop ( Fig. 8A ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12101307" target="_blank">12101307</a>]<br></li>
<li>Mutational Analysis of the Transcriptional Regulator GcvA : Amino Acids Important for Activation , Repression , and DNA Binding ALISSA D. JOURDAN AND GEORGE V. STAUFFER * Department of Microbiology , The University of Iowa , Iowa City , Iowa 52242 Received 6 April 1998/Accepted 22 July 1998 The GcvA protein is required for both glycine-mediated activation and purine-mediated repression of the gcvTHP operon .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9733689" target="_blank">9733689</a>]<br></li>
<li>This conclusion is supported by results with lysogen GS1003XTlac ( A-466 +8 C +10 A ) , where both Lrp and GcvA are nonfunctional and no significant purine-mediated repression is observed .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=7928983" target="_blank">7928983</a>]<br></li>
<li>This repression of gc ~ s is considered to be mediated through the GcvA protein itself [ 32 ] .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=8522138" target="_blank">8522138</a>]<br></li>
<li>The C-ter 14 aa 's of the GcvA protein are required for purine-mediated repression of gcv .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9733689" target="_blank">9733689</a>]<br></li>
<li>A PurR-independent mechanism for purine repression of gcv is mediated by the GcvA protein .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=7665470" target="_blank">7665470</a>]<br></li>
<li>The ﬁnal objective of this study was to determine which amino acids in GcvA are involved in purine-mediated repression .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9733689" target="_blank">9733689</a>]<br></li>
<li>The results are consistent with the previous hypothesis that GcvA site 1 is primarily involved in GcvA-mediated repression .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11065369" target="_blank">11065369</a>]<br></li>
<li>The site 1 GcvA binding site might not be involved in activation of gcv by glycine but in some manner is necessary for repression of gcv by purines , perhaps by binding of some cofactor or other protein and interaction with GcvA at sites 2 or 3 to prevent transcription by RNA polymerase .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=7665470" target="_blank">7665470</a>]<br></li>
<li>In this study , mutations were created in GcvA binding site 1 to determine which nucleotides are necessary for GcvA binding and the effects of these mutations on GcvA-mediated repression and activation .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11065369" target="_blank">11065369</a>]<br></li>
<li>PCR-generated mutations in any of the three GcvA binding sites in gcv decreased GcvA-mediated activation and repression of gcv .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=7665470" target="_blank">7665470</a>]<br></li>
<li>One model ﬁtting the data presented is that binding of GcvA to site 3 is required for activation and repression of gcv , while site 2 stabilizes the binding of GcvA to site 3 .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=7665470" target="_blank">7665470</a>]<br></li>
<li>The repression observed in the GS852 IHF-C and IHF-D results are also consistent with a model where Lrp lysogens are due to IHF binding and bending the gcv normally plays primarily a structural role , and GcvA is DNA , this activation and repression should not be the gcv-specific regulatory protein .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10217490" target="_blank">10217490</a>]<br></li>
<li>The results of this study partially deﬁne regions of GcvA involved in activation , repression , and DNA binding and demonstrate that these functions of GcvA are genetically separable .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9733689" target="_blank">9733689</a>]<br></li>
<li>The ﬁrst objective of this study was to identify single amino acid substitutions in GcvA that result in the loss of transcriptional activation of the gcv promoter but not the loss of DNA binding or repression .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9733689" target="_blank">9733689</a>]<br></li>
<li>In addition , positive control mutants were isolated in gcvA that decreased GcvA 's ability to activate gcv transcription , but that did not affect DNA binding or GcvA-mediated repression ( Jourdan & Stauffer , 1998 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12101307" target="_blank">12101307</a>]<br></li>
<li>GcvR s ability to repress is dependent on GcvA [ 4 ] and genetic and biochemical evidence suggests that GcvR interacts directly with GcvA rather than binding to DNA to cause repression [ 5,6 ] .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15621456" target="_blank">15621456</a>]<br></li>
<li>Preliminary evidence suggests that GcvR interacts directly with GcvA rather than binding gcv DNA ( A. Ghrist , unpublished results ) , but the mechanism by which GcvR causes repression is unknown .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11065369" target="_blank">11065369</a>]<br></li>
<li>The most severe allele examined that alters both GcvA binding and repression is the 1-B mutant , with ﬁve base changes ( Fig. 4 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11065369" target="_blank">11065369</a>]<br></li>
<li>These changes result in about a fourfold decrease in GcvA binding afinity in vitro when compared to WT site 1 ( Fig. 5 ) , and in vivo caused a sixfold loss of GcvA-mediated repression when cells were grown in GMinosine ( Table 3 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11065369" target="_blank">11065369</a>]<br></li>
<li>We expected that one or more of these nucleotides would be required for GcvA binding and repression , and for general promoter strength independent of GcvA .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11065369" target="_blank">11065369</a>]<br></li>
