<li>Since glycine does not signiﬁcantly affect GcvA 's ability to-bind or bend DNA , we wanted to determine how glycine is involved in the activation mechanism .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12101307" target="_blank">12101307</a>]<br></li>
<li>la ) , as well as the strict requirement that GcvA and Lrp proteins bind on the correct surface of the DNA relative to RNAP for both activation and repression , make it likely that DNA looping is part of the mechanism of gcu operon regulation .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9611815" target="_blank">9611815</a>]<br></li>
<li>Activation and repression by GcvA requires Lrp , presumably to bend the DNA appropriately ( Stauffer & Stauffer , 1998a , b , 1999 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11065369" target="_blank">11065369</a>]<br></li>
<li>Since the mutations in the conserved 5 `` - CTAAT-3 `` sequence of site 1 alter repression to varying degrees but reduce GcvA 's binding afinity less than twofold , it is possible that some other function , such as DNA bending , is affected by mutations in the region that leads to altered regulation .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11065369" target="_blank">11065369</a>]<br></li>
<li>Thus , although the bp changes only resulted in a small decrease in the ability of GcvA to-bind to site 1 , they signiﬁcantly altered GcvA-induced bending of the DNA .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12101307" target="_blank">12101307</a>]<br></li>
<li>To determine whether the Phe at aa31 of GcvA was required for activation or if the Leu substitution at this position altered protein structure , thus diminishing GcvA-mediated activation , codon 31 was site speciﬁcally changed to an alanine ( Ala ) ( Materials and Methods ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9733689" target="_blank">9733689</a>]<br></li>
<li>Since GcvA-mediated activation requires GcvA bound to sites 2 and 3 , located 214 -- 271 bp upstream of the transcription start site , it is reasonable to assume that a looped nucleoprotein structure is required for an appropriate GcvA -RCB- RNAP contact for activation ( Fig. 8B ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12101307" target="_blank">12101307</a>]<br></li>
<li>The isolation of an allele-specific suppressor in gcvA that restores activation would support a direct interaction between GcvA and RNAP .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9802028" target="_blank">9802028</a>]<br></li>
<li>If the V32A substitution no longer allows multimerization of GcvA , this would suggest that the residues involved in multimerization and the residues involved in activation are adjacent in the GcvA protein .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9733689" target="_blank">9733689</a>]<br></li>
<li>These results suggest that GcvA also negatively autoregulates its own synthesis .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=8188587" target="_blank">8188587</a>]<br></li>
<li>These results suggest that both activation and repression of the gcvT : : lac2 fusion are face-of-the-helix dependent and require a precise stereospecific orientation of either GcvA , Lrp or both , relative to the gcu promoter .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9611815" target="_blank">9611815</a>]<br></li>
<li>These results suggest that the ability of the g c v T : : l a c Z fusion to be regulated in response to normal physiological signals for activation and repression was altered by increased levels of GcvA .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10463182" target="_blank">10463182</a>]<br></li>
<li>Our results are consistent with GcvA interacting with the RNAP a subunit to activate PgcvT and interacting with the RNAP r subunit to activate PgcvB .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15621456" target="_blank">15621456</a>]<br></li>
<li>We are constructing and testin additional mutations in the GcvA H -- T -- H region to determine if there are other amino acids in GcvA that are required for activation of both the PgcvT and PgcvB promoters , or are speciﬁc for only one of the promoters .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15621456" target="_blank">15621456</a>]<br></li>
<li>Previous genetic results showed that a region of GcvA that is required for activation of PgcvT , deﬁned by the gcvA-F31L positive control mutation , is also required for activation of the PgcvB promoter [ 2,23 ] .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15621456" target="_blank">15621456</a>]<br></li>
<li>Since GcvA contacts the aCTD to activate PgcvT [ 24 ] , we tested if the aCTD is also required for activation of PgcvB .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15621456" target="_blank">15621456</a>]<br></li>
<li>Thus , although it is possible that part of the effects of the a mutations could be mediated through Lrp and CRP , the results are more consistent with a GcvA Æ aCTD interaction likely being required for GcvA-mediated activation at the PgcvT promoter .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15621456" target="_blank">15621456</a>]<br></li>
<li>Thus , the GcvA Æ aCTD interaction required for GcvA activation of the PgcvT promoter is not required for GcvA activation of the PgcvB promoter .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15621456" target="_blank">15621456</a>]<br></li>
<li>These results suggest that a GcvA Æ r70 interaction is likely required at the PgcvB promoter , but is not required for GcvA activation of the PgcvT promoter .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15621456" target="_blank">15621456</a>]<br></li>
