<li>Furthermore , this constitutive expression is strictly dependent on GcvA activation , as the gcvR , gcvA double mutant lysogen GS1131lgcvB ± lacZ shows low , non-inducible b-galactosidase activity .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10972807" target="_blank">10972807</a>]<br></li>
<li>GcvA activates and represses expression of gcvT-lacZ , and it is likely that both functions of GcvA are responsible for the basal levels of gcvT-lacZ expression in GM medium .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10074087" target="_blank">10074087</a>]<br></li>
