<li>The cyclic AMP receptor protein is dependent on GcvA for regulation of the gcv operon .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11065369" target="_blank">11065369</a>, <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12101307" target="_blank">12101307</a>]<br></li></div>
<li>e-mail : george-stauffer@uiowa.edu Department of UniversityOf GcvA and Lrp are both necessary for activation of the gcv operon .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9802028" target="_blank">9802028</a>]<br></li>
<li>An Ala substitution at aa31 of GcvA showed that the Phe at this position in wt GcvA provides a critical side chain required for glycinemediated activation of the gcv operon .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9733689" target="_blank">9733689</a>]<br></li>
<li>All of the gcvR mutations identiﬁed in this study that result in a decrease in repression of the gcv operon as well as a decrease in heterodimerization lie in the Cterminal half of the protein , suggesting that this region is involved in an interaction with GcvA .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11495998" target="_blank">11495998</a>]<br></li>
<li>Finally , although unable to activate gcv transcription , the Cterminal half of GcvA is able to interfere with GcvRmediated repression of wild-type GcvA , probably by titrating the available antiactivator , leading to constitutive activation of the operon ( Table 4 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11495998" target="_blank">11495998</a>]<br></li>
<li>To define domains of the GcvA protein involved in activation and repression , a genetic selection was designed to screen for mutations in gcuA that produce proteins able to activate but unable to repress the gcu operon .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10463182" target="_blank">10463182</a>]<br></li>
<li>Both modes of regulation by GcvA require at least two additional protein factors : ( i ) GcvR is a negative-acting protein that is hypothesized to interact with GcvA , antagonizing activation of gcvTHP by GcvA and promoting repression ( Ghrist and Stauffer , 1995a ) ; ( ii ) Lrp is a global regulatory protein affecting the control of many genes , including gcvTHP ( Lin et al. , 1992 ; Calvo and Matthews , 1994 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10972807" target="_blank">10972807</a>]<br></li>
<li>Transcription of the gcv operon is under the control of three global regulatory proteins [ Lrp , PurR and cAMP-receptor protein ( CRP ) ] and two gcv-speciﬁc transcriptional-regulatory proteins ( GcvA and GcvR ) ( Ghrist & Stauffer , 1995 ; Lin et al. , 1992 ; Stauffer & Stauffer , 1994 ; Wilson et al. , 1993a ; Wilson & Stauffer , 1994 ; Wonderling & Stauffer , 1999 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12101307" target="_blank">12101307</a>]<br></li>
<li>It should be noted that the 1 ± 5 -- 2-fold repression observed in GMinosine medium is due to the PurR repressor , which has been shown to repress transcription of the gcv operon independently of GcvA -RCB- GcvR-mediated repression ( Wilson et al. , 1993a ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11495998" target="_blank">11495998</a>]<br></li>
<li>GcvA synthesis itself is autoregulated by the repression of its own promoter ( Wilson and Stauffer , 1994 ; Wilson et al. , 1995 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10972807" target="_blank">10972807</a>]<br></li>
<li>PurR-mediated repression is independent of the GcvA and GcvR proteins ( Wilson et al. , 1993a ; Ghrist & Stauffer , 1995a ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9802028" target="_blank">9802028</a>]<br></li>
<li>GcvA plays a dual role in the regulation of gcv , since it is also required for six - to sevenfold activation of gcv when glycine is included in the growth media ( 37 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=7665470" target="_blank">7665470</a>]<br></li>
<li>GcvA , n member of the LysR family of transcriptional reguliitors ( Schell , 1993 ) , plays a dual role in gcu regulation by mediating a fivefold , PurR-independent repression o f gc-11 expression in the presence of purines and : I six - t o sevenfold activation in the presence of glycine ( Wilson ct al. , 1993a , b ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10463182" target="_blank">10463182</a>]<br></li>
<li>GcvA activates gcv expression when cells are grown in the presence of glycine and mediates a PurR-independent repression of gcv when cells are grown in the presence of inosine but without glycine ( 44 , 45 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10074087" target="_blank">10074087</a>]<br></li>
<li>GcvA activates gcv expression in the presence of exogenous glycine and represses gcv in the presence of exog-enous purines without glycine ( 30 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=7928983" target="_blank">7928983</a>]<br></li>
<li>Transcription of the gcv operon is activated by the GcvA protein in the presence of excess glycine .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11495998" target="_blank">11495998</a>]<br></li>
<li>GcvA activates the operon in the presence of glycine and represses the operon in its absence .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12101307" target="_blank">12101307</a>]<br></li>
<li>The Both Lrp and GcvA are required for expression of the GS852 +2 l - , , , lysogen showed about a 2-fold higher gcv operon ( Stauffer & Stauffer , 1994 ; Wilson et al. , basal level of expression in G M medium than the 1993b ; Lin et al. , 1992 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9802028" target="_blank">9802028</a>]<br></li>
<li>Both gcv and gcvB are activated by GcvA in response to glycine and repressed by GcvA1GcvR in the absence of glycine ( Wilson et al. , 1993 ; Stauffer & Stauffer , 1994 ; Urbanowski et al. , 2000 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=18312576" target="_blank">18312576</a>]<br></li>
<li>Transcription of the gcvTHP operon is activated by the GcvA protein when cellular glycine levels are high ; when glycine is limiting , GcvA actively represses the expression of the operon ( Wilson et al. , 1993 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10972807" target="_blank">10972807</a>]<br></li>
<li>When glycine is limiting , GcvA actively represses expression of the operon ; this repression is more severe in the presence of excess purines ( Wilson et al. , 1993a , b ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11495998" target="_blank">11495998</a>]<br></li>
<li>GcvA also represses the gcv operon over a ﬁvefold range when the purine inosine is added to the growth medium ( Wilson et al. , 1993a ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11065369" target="_blank">11065369</a>]<br></li>
<li>GcvA acts as an activator of gcv expression when glycine is present in the growth medium , causing a six - to sevenfold induction ( Wilson et al. , 1993b ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11065369" target="_blank">11065369</a>]<br></li>
<li>GcvA , a member of the LysR family of transcriptional-regulatory proteins , functions as an activator of the gcv operon in the presence of exogenous glycine and as a repressor of the operon in the absence of glycine ( Wilson et al. , 1993a , b ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12101307" target="_blank">12101307</a>]<br></li>
