<li>gcvA allele * β-Galactosidase activity † in cells grown in : ‡ GM Glycine Inosine GcvA mutants unable to repress gcv expression are impaired in their ability to interact with GcvR None 21 To test whether the gcvA mutants described above are defective in their ability to interact with GcvR , each mutant allele was cloned into pMS604 and its interaction with GcvR measured using the LexA heterodimerization system .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11495998" target="_blank">11495998</a>]<br></li>
<li>Isolation of gcvR mutants unable to properly repress the gcv operon To determine if gcvR mutants unable to properly repress gcv expression might also be defective in their ability to interact with GcvA , the following strategy was used to isolate gcvR mutants impaired in their ability to negatively regulate the gcv operon .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11495998" target="_blank">11495998</a>]<br></li>
<li>GcvA functions to both activate and repress gcv expression ( 30 , 31 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9733689" target="_blank">9733689</a>]<br></li>
<li>Isolation of GcvA mutants refractory to inhibition by GcvR In a previous study , two gcvA mutants that are able to activate but not repress gcv expression were isolated but not characterized ( Jourdan & Stauffer , 1998 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11495998" target="_blank">11495998</a>]<br></li>
<li>We have designed a genetic screen to isolate mutations in the coding region of gcvA that would render the GcvA protein either unable to repress gcv in the presence of inosine or , alternatively , unable to activate gcv in the presence of glycine .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10463182" target="_blank">10463182</a>]<br></li>
<li>These results suggest that the mutations present in the lgcvT-lacZ site 1 phage partially affected the ability of GcvA to act as a repressor of gcv when cells were grown in the presence of inosine .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=7665470" target="_blank">7665470</a>]<br></li>
<li>These data suggest that the opposite effects of GcvA on gcv expression are mediated through the GcvA protein itself , perhaps by the binding of different cofactors to specific sites .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=8188587" target="_blank">8188587</a>]<br></li>
<li>These results suggest that GcvA and GcvR act together at the gcv control region to directly repress gcv expression .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11495998" target="_blank">11495998</a>]<br></li>
<li>These results and the results of the GMS assays suggest that glycine probably does not interact directly with GcvA to activate the gcv operon .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12101307" target="_blank">12101307</a>]<br></li>
<li>These results led us to propose a model in which GcvA homocomplexes function as activators , whilst GcvA -RCB- GcvR heterocomplexes function as repressors .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11495998" target="_blank">11495998</a>]<br></li>
<li>A model was previously proposed t o explain how GcvA and GcvR might interact to regulate gcu expression , where GcvA homocomplexes function as activators and GcvA-GcvR heterocomplexes function as repressors ( Christ & Stauffer , 199.5 ; Wilson & Stauffer , 1994 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10463182" target="_blank">10463182</a>]<br></li>
<li>T h e amount o f GcvA protein required to-bind and shift the + 13A and + 1SG ~ i u A Modifying the level of gcvA expression affects gcv regulation Previous studies have shown that regulation of a gcvT : : l a c 2 fusion is sensitive to the level of GcvA in the cell ( Ghrist & Stauffer , 1995 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10463182" target="_blank">10463182</a>]<br></li>
<li>Second , GcvA induces constitutive expression of a gcvT : : lacZ fusion in the absence of glycine if GcvR is inactivated , a growth condition that results in a partial glycine auxotrophy ( Table 2 ; Ghrist & Stauffer , 1995 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12101307" target="_blank">12101307</a>]<br></li>
<li>The GcvR protein is a negative regulator of gcvT : : lacZ expression and its ability to repress is dependent on a functional GcvA protein ( Ghrist & Stauffer , 1995 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9611815" target="_blank">9611815</a>]<br></li>
<li>In this strain , GcvA can no longer repress gcvT : : lacZ expression ( Ghrist & Stauffer , 1995 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11065369" target="_blank">11065369</a>]<br></li>
<li>Since GcvR requires a functional GcvA protein for its negative effect ( Ghrist & Stauffer , 1995 ) , GcvR might function in this model to influence which type of protein-protein interaction occurs as a result of the DNA loop , or the degree of the DNA bend .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9611815" target="_blank">9611815</a>]<br></li>
<li>GcvR is also involved in negative regulation of the gcv op-eron , and the ability of GcvR to repress gcv requires a functional GcvA protein , even when GcvR is overexpressed ( 6 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9733689" target="_blank">9733689</a>]<br></li>
<li>Since GcvA activates a gcvT : : lacZ fusion in the absence of GcvR , and GcvR-mediated repression is dependent on a functional GcvA protein , a model was proposed that GcvA homo-oligomers activate the gcv operon , whereas GcvA -RCB- GcvR hetero-oligomers repress the gcv operon ( Ghrist & Stauffer , 1995 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11065369" target="_blank">11065369</a>]<br></li>
				<label class="ACT_collapse_similarity" for="act_similarity_240">
The GcvR protein negatively regulates the gcv operon ( Ghrist & Stauffer , 1995 ) ; its ability to repress is dependent on a functional GcvA protein .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9611815" target="_blank">9611815</a>]<br></label>
<input id="act_similarity_240", type="checkbox">
<div class="ACT_similar">
<li>The GcvR protein also negatively regulates the gcv operon , although its ability to repress is dependent on a functional GcvA protein ( Ghrist & Stauffer , 199Sa ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9802028" target="_blank">9802028</a>]<br></li></div>
<li>The regulation of the Y. pestis gcvB gene was tested with respect to the effects of glycine and purine supplementation to the growth medium and with respect to the GcvR and GcvA proteins and the GcvB RNAs .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=16768793" target="_blank">16768793</a>]<br></li>
<li>Conclusion In summary , the Y. pestis gcvB gene is activated by the GcvA protein and repressed by the GcvR protein .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=16768793" target="_blank">16768793</a>]<br></li>
<li>Transcription from the gcvB promoter is activated by the GcvA protein and repressed by the GcvR protein , the transcriptional-regulators of the gcvTHP operon encoding the enzymes of the glycine cleavage system .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10972807" target="_blank">10972807</a>]<br></li>
<li>Both gcvTHP and gcvB are activated by the GcvA protein in response to glycine and repressed by the GcvA + GcvR proteins in the absence of glycine ; this repression is enhanced in the presence of Corresponding author .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15621456" target="_blank">15621456</a>]<br></li>
<li>Regulation of the Y. pestis gcvB gene The E. coli gcvB gene is activated by GcvA in the presence of glycine and repressed by GcvA + GcvR in its absence ; this repression is enhanced by the addition of purines [ 11 ] .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=16768793" target="_blank">16768793</a>]<br></li>
<li>The decision by GcvA to either induce or repress gcvTHP transcription is sensitive to the level of the activator ( or to the GcvA : GcvR ratio ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10972807" target="_blank">10972807</a>]<br></li>
<li>In E. coli , GcvA also activates the gcvTHP operon and GcvA + GcvR repress the operon [ 17,18 ] .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=16768793" target="_blank">16768793</a>]<br></li>
<li>Finally , it is shown that the C-terminal half of GcvA is involved in its interaction with GcvR , whilst the entire GcvR protein appears to be necessary for heterodimerization .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11495998" target="_blank">11495998</a>]<br></li>
<li>In addition , it was shown that gcvR-lacZ expression is neither regulated by the glycine cleavage activator protein ( GcvA ) nor autogenously regulated by GcvR .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9537378" target="_blank">9537378</a>]<br></li>
<li>Using a LexA-based system for analysing protein heterodimerization , it is shown that GcvR interacts directly with GcvA in vivo to repress gcvTHP expression .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11495998" target="_blank">11495998</a>]<br></li>
<li>In the absence of glycine , inosine repressed expression more than ninefold ; this was shown previously to be a result of a combined repression by PurR and GcvA .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=7928983" target="_blank">7928983</a>]<br></li>
<li>In the absence of glycine , GcvR binds directly to GcvA , forming a repression complex .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12101307" target="_blank">12101307</a>]<br></li>
<li>In glycine-supplemented cultures , GcvR repression is relieved , and GcvA activates gcv expression ( 8 , 28 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9537378" target="_blank">9537378</a>]<br></li>
<li>In purine-supplemented cultures , both GcvA and GcvR are required to mediate a PurR-independent repression of gcv ( 8 , 27 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9537378" target="_blank">9537378</a>]<br></li>
<li>However , overexpression of gcvR re-established purinemediated repression of the gcvT : : lacZfusion , supporting the model for gcv regulation that suggests the need for a relatively constant GcvA to GcvR ratio for appropriate regulation of gcv expression in response to glycine and purine availability .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10463182" target="_blank">10463182</a>]<br></li>
<li>Since overproduction of GcvA leads to activation of gcv , while overproduction of GcvR results in repression of gcv ( 8 ) , it is possible that glycine and inosine alter gcv expression indirectly by altering the ratio of GcvA to GcvR .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9537378" target="_blank">9537378</a>]<br></li>
<li>One possible explanation for the two different effects of GcvA on gcv expression ( i.e. , glycine induction and inosine repression ) is that gcvA itself is regulated in glycine inosine .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=8188587" target="_blank">8188587</a>]<br></li>
<li>Since the co-inducer glycine binds GcvR rather than the activator GcvA , it is possible that glycine 's role is to prevent a GcvA -RCB- GcvR interaction required for repression , permitting GcvA to function as an activator .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12101307" target="_blank">12101307</a>]<br></li>
<li>Thus , glycine does not act as a classical co-activator in this system , but rather through a mechanism of de-repression by binding to GcvR and preventing GcvR from interacting with GcvA to block GcvA 's activator function .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12101307" target="_blank">12101307</a>]<br></li>
<li>However , we do not know if the repression mediated by the GcvR protein requires the GcvA -RCB- site 1 interaction or if GcvR represses through a separate mechanism .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11065369" target="_blank">11065369</a>]<br></li>
<li>The dominance of glycine to purines in the regulatory mechanism , and the ability of glycine to disrupt the GcvA -RCB- GcvR interaction are consistent with a GcvA -RCB- GcvR complex being necessary for purine-mediated repression .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12101307" target="_blank">12101307</a>]<br></li>
<li>In this case , the binding of glycine to GcvR prevents this protein from interacting wit GcvA to block activation ( 26 , 32 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=16997959" target="_blank">16997959</a>]<br></li>
<li>GcvA binds to a single region in the gcvB control region from bp 29 to 76 relative to the transcription initiation site ( Fig. 1 ( b ) ) [ 12 ] , and binding of GcvA to this region is required for both GcvA-mediated activation in the presence of glycine and GcvA Æ GcvR-mediated repression in the absence of glycine [ 16 ] .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15621456" target="_blank">15621456</a>]<br></li>
<li>Thus , GcvA is still required for both glycine-mediated activation and inosine-mediated repression of the + ll - , , , and +21 -213 fusions .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9802028" target="_blank">9802028</a>]<br></li>
<li>Published by Elsevier B.V. All rights reserved doi :10.1016 / j.femsle .2004.11.027 GcvA Æ GcvR-mediated repression of the gcvTHP operon , whereas only sites 3 and 2 appear to be required for GcvA-mediated activation of the operon in response to glycine [ 12 ] .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15621456" target="_blank">15621456</a>]<br></li>
<li>Rather , glycine binds to GcvR , disrupting a GcvA/GcvR interaction required for repression and allowing GcvA activation of the gcvTHP operon .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12101307" target="_blank">12101307</a>]<br></li>
<li>However , GcvR-mediated repression is dependent on a functional GcvA protein ; gcvA mutants no longer show GcvR-mediated purine repression , and the levels of gcvTlacZ expression in a gcvA mutant overexpressing gcvR on a multicopy plasmid are no lower than in the gcvA gcvR double mutant ( 6 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9733689" target="_blank">9733689</a>]<br></li>
<li>Reduced gcvB : : lacZ expression in the rpoD m is not due to increased GcvR levels or decreased G levels utants cvA Activation of gcvB requires a functional GcvA protein and repression requires a functional GcvR protein [ 2 ] .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15621456" target="_blank">15621456</a>]<br></li>
<li>Transcriptional repression by LexA heterodimer formation of GcvA and GcvR .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11495998" target="_blank">11495998</a>]<br></li>
