			<label class="collapse_RP" for="_4"><font size="5px">Processes regulated by GcvA</font></label>
				<input id="_4" type="checkbox">
				<div class="RP"><br><ul><li>For comparison , Fig. 2B shows sequence alignments within DBDs of some LTTRs ( CbnR , CysB , OxyR and GcvA ) and residues involved in DNA binding ( blue ) or pc function ( red ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15255893" target="_blank">15255893</a>]<br></li>
<li>A wide range of environmental stimuli affect the expression of the sRNAs including oxidative stress ( OxyR activates OxyS ) ; cell surface stress ( RcsB activates RprA ) ; glycine status of the cell ( GcvA activates GcvB ) ; osmotic imbalance ( OmpR activates OmrA/B ) ; quality of carbon source/growth rate [ McaS ; transcription factor ( s ) unknown ] ; low temperature [ DsrA ; transcription factor ( s ) unknown ] and O tension ( ArcA-ArcB 2 represses ArzA under anaerobic conditions ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=22250746" target="_blank">22250746</a>]<br></li>
<li>Regulation of the gcv operon by GcvA and GcvR is part of a growing number of prokaryotic regulatory systems involving an activator -RCB- antiactivator complex , including TraR -RCB- TraM regulation of conjugal transfer of the Ti plasmid in Agrobacterium tumefaciens ( Hwang et al. , 1999 ) , NifA -RCB- NifL regulation of nitrogen ﬁxation in Klebsiella pneumoniae ( Narberhaus et al. , 1995 ) , ComK -RCB- MecA -RCB- ClpC regulation of competence in Ba-cillus subtilis ( Turgay et al. , 1998 ) and CRP -RCB- CytR regulation of operons encoding the nucleoside-transport and biosynthesis enzymes ( Valentin-Hansen et al. , 1996 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11495998" target="_blank">11495998</a>]<br></li>
<li>Y. pestis gcvA encodes an activator protein for gcvB expression Since activation of the Y. pestis gcvBYp +53 fusion in E. coli was dependent on GcvA ( Table 2 ) , we determined if the Y. pestis gcvA gene also encodes an activator protein for gcvB expression .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=16768793" target="_blank">16768793</a>]<br></li>
<li>A possible explanation for CRP 's dependence on GcvA is that CRP regulates expression of the gcvA gene and indirectly affects expression of gcvT-lacZ .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10074087" target="_blank">10074087</a>]<br></li>
<li>In addition , GcvA is known to require the gcvR gene product for its role as a repressor ( 12 ) , raising the possibilities that CRP also regulates expression of gcvR and indirectly alters gcvT-lacZ expression .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10074087" target="_blank">10074087</a>]<br></li>
<li>Lrp , a global regulator for many genes involved in amino-acid-metabolism [ 13 ] , binds to multiple sites upstream of the PgcvT promoter , from bp 92 to 229 ( Fig. 1 ( a ) ) and plays a structural role in gcvTHP regulation , bending the DNA to allow GcvA to function as either an activator or repressor [ 14 ] .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15621456" target="_blank">15621456</a>]<br></li>
<li>One model proposed for gcv regulation is that Lrp plays a structural role , bending the DNA to allow GcvA to function as either an activator or a repressor in response to environmental signals .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10217490" target="_blank">10217490</a>]<br></li>
<li>S2 ) , which is presumably regulated by several factors , including the HexR activator , the glycine-responsive activator GcvA , and the previously unknown regulator of purine-metabolism operated by binding to PUR-boxes .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=21849503" target="_blank">21849503</a>]<br></li>
<li>e-mail : george-stauffer ( iuiowa.edu Department of Microbiology , The University of Iowa , Iowa City , IA 52242 , USA The GcvA protein both activates and represses the gcv operon and negatively regulates its own transcription .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10463182" target="_blank">10463182</a>]<br></li>
<li>The GcvA protein is responsible for controlling gcv operon expression in two distinct ways .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10074087" target="_blank">10074087</a>]<br></li>
<li>The GcvR protein also negatively regulates the gcv operon , although its ability to repress is dependent on a functional GcvA protein ( Ghrist & Stauffer , 199Sa ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9802028" target="_blank">9802028</a>]<br></li>
<li>GcvR is also involved in negative regulation of the gcv op-eron , and the ability of GcvR to repress gcv requires a functional GcvA protein , even when GcvR is overexpressed ( 6 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9733689" target="_blank">9733689</a>]<br></li>
<li>Both modes of regulation by GcvA require at least two additional protein factors : ( i ) GcvR is a negative-acting protein that is hypothesized to interact with GcvA , antagonizing activation of gcvTHP by GcvA and promoting repression ( Ghrist and Stauffer , 1995a ) ; ( ii ) Lrp is a global regulatory protein affecting the control of many genes , including gcvTHP ( Lin et al. , 1992 ; Calvo and Matthews , 1994 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10972807" target="_blank">10972807</a>]<br></li>
<li>Whether the Y. pestis GcvA and GcvR proteins also regulate the Y. pestis gcvTHP operon , or have additional regulatory roles , awaits further investigation .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=16768793" target="_blank">16768793</a>]<br></li>
<li>It is unlikely that the resultant action of the GcvA activator on both the gcvTHP operon and gcvB is simply a response to maintain glycine stasis , i.e. that there is a linking of the inducibility of the Gcv system under conditions of excess exogenous glycine to repression of the peptide-transport systems that may otherwise accumulate glycine-rich peptides .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10972807" target="_blank">10972807</a>]<br></li>
<li>To define amino acids i n GcvA important for irs repressor function , we attempted to isolate gczjA mutnnts th : it encoded proteins that could no longer repress g c i ~ T : : lacZ expression in the presence of purines but could activate expression in the presence of glycine .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10463182" target="_blank">10463182</a>]<br></li>
<li>GcvA also negatively regulates its own promoter independently of glycine or purine supplementation .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=7665470" target="_blank">7665470</a>]<br></li>
<li>However , overexpression of gcvR re-established purinemediated repression of the gcvT : : lacZfusion , supporting the model for gcv regulation that suggests the need for a relatively constant GcvA to GcvR ratio for appropriate regulation of gcv expression in response to glycine and purine availability .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10463182" target="_blank">10463182</a>]<br></li>
<li>uiowa.edu Department of The Escherichia coli gcvTHP operon is under control of the LysR-type transcriptional regulator GcvA .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12101307" target="_blank">12101307</a>]<br></li>
