<div class="TU_similar">
<li>The GcvR protein also negatively regulates the gcv operon , although its ability to repress is dependent on a functional GcvA protein ( Ghrist & Stauffer , 199Sa ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9802028" target="_blank">9802028</a>]<br></li></div>
<li>Second , GcvA induces constitutive expression of a gcvT : : lacZ fusion in the absence of glycine if GcvR is inactivated , a growth condition that results in a partial glycine auxotrophy ( Table 2 ; Ghrist & Stauffer , 1995 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12101307" target="_blank">12101307</a>]<br></li>
<li>The GcvR protein is a negative regulator of gcvT : : lacZ expression and its ability to repress is dependent on a functional GcvA protein ( Ghrist & Stauffer , 1995 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9611815" target="_blank">9611815</a>]<br></li>
<li>In this strain , GcvA can no longer repress gcvT : : lacZ expression ( Ghrist & Stauffer , 1995 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11065369" target="_blank">11065369</a>]<br></li>
<li>Y. pestis gcvA encodes an activator protein for gcvB expression Since activation of the Y. pestis gcvBYp +53 fusion in E. coli was dependent on GcvA ( Table 2 ) , we determined if the Y. pestis gcvA gene also encodes an activator protein for gcvB expression .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=16768793" target="_blank">16768793</a>]<br></li>
<li>The GcvA protein is required for expression of both the gcvTHP ( PgcvT ) and gcvB ( PgcvB ) promoters .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15621456" target="_blank">15621456</a>]<br></li>
<li>The RNA polymerase holoenzyme was examined for its role in transcription activation of the gcvTHP operon and the gcvB gene by the GcvA protein .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15621456" target="_blank">15621456</a>]<br></li>
<li>Keywords : gcvTHP operon ; gcvB gene ; GcvA activator protein ; RNA polymerase 1 .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15621456" target="_blank">15621456</a>]<br></li>
<li>In turn , the transcription of gcvB is positively regulated by the GcvA protein , the major transcription factor of the glycine cleavage system ( 32 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=22020646" target="_blank">22020646</a>]<br></li>
<li>Transcription from the gcvB promoter is activated by the GcvA protein and repressed by the GcvR protein , the transcriptional regulators of the gcvTHP operon encoding the enzymes of the glycine cleavage system .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10972807" target="_blank">10972807</a>]<br></li>
<li>Conclusion In summary , the Y. pestis gcvB gene is activated by the GcvA protein and repressed by the GcvR protein .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=16768793" target="_blank">16768793</a>]<br></li>
<li>Both gcvTHP and gcvB are activated by the GcvA protein in response to glycine and repressed by the GcvA + GcvR proteins in the absence of glycine ; this repression is enhanced in the presence of Corresponding author .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15621456" target="_blank">15621456</a>]<br></li>
<li>Regulation of the Y. pestis gcvB gene The E. coli gcvB gene is activated by GcvA in the presence of glycine and repressed by GcvA + GcvR in its absence ; this repression is enhanced by the addition of purines [ 11 ] .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=16768793" target="_blank">16768793</a>]<br></li>
<li>Transcription of the gcv operon is activated by the GcvA protein in the presence of excess glycine .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11495998" target="_blank">11495998</a>]<br></li>
<li>GcvA activates the operon in the presence of glycine and represses the operon in its absence .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12101307" target="_blank">12101307</a>]<br></li>
<li>The GcvA protein activates expression of the gcv operon in glycine-supplemented medium and is also necessary for PurR-independent repression of the operon when cells are grown in the presence of inosine but without glycine ( Wilson et al. , 1993a , b ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9611815" target="_blank">9611815</a>]<br></li>
<li>Transcription of the gcvTHP operon is activated by the GcvA protein when cellular glycine levels are high ; when glycine is limiting , GcvA actively represses the expression of the operon ( Wilson et al. , 1993 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10972807" target="_blank">10972807</a>]<br></li>
<li>When glycine is limiting , GcvA actively represses expression of the operon ; this repression is more severe in the presence of excess purines ( Wilson et al. , 1993a , b ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11495998" target="_blank">11495998</a>]<br></li>
<li>GcvA synthesis itself is autoregulated by the repression of its own promoter ( Wilson and Stauffer , 1994 ; Wilson et al. , 1995 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10972807" target="_blank">10972807</a>]<br></li>
<li>Both gcv and gcvB are activated by GcvA in response to glycine and repressed by GcvA1GcvR in the absence of glycine ( Wilson et al. , 1993 ; Stauffer & Stauffer , 1994 ; Urbanowski et al. , 2000 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=18312576" target="_blank">18312576</a>]<br></li>
